    <body>
        
        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down, | Beckenham, Kent.</hi> | (<hi rend="print">Railway Station | Orpington. S.E.R.</hi>)</placeName>
                    <date>May 8<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>. 1880</date>
                    <salute>Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>I am very much obliged to you for your kind note.<ref target="#foot.f1"/> Should I ever bring out a new Edit. of my Descent of Man or Expression of the Emotions, which is not probable, your information will be useful to me.—<ref target="#foot.f2"/></p> 
                    <p>Dear Sir | Yours faithfully &amp; obliged | Ch. Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="tnotes">
                <note xml:id="tnote.n1">0.1 (<hi rend="italic">Railway … S.E.R.</hi>)] <hi rend="italic">parentheses added</hi> </note>
            </div>
        </div>
        
        
        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">See <ref target="./DCP-LETT-12598.xml">letter from James Dixon, 7 May 1880</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">No new editions of <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_1966.xml"><hi rend="italic">Descent</hi></ref> or <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_2400.xml"><hi rend="italic">Expression</hi></ref> were published in CD’s lifetime.</note> 
        </div> 
     
